text.section:
In determining whether a policy is legible the commissioner shall consider, in addition to the requirements of subsection (1) of this section relating to type face size and style, the following factors:
Margin size;
Contrast and legibility of the color of the ink and paper;
The amount and use of space to separate sections of the policy;
The use of contrasting titles or headings for sections or similar aids; and
Any additional factors relevant to legibility which the commissioner may prescribe by regulation.
